api.ts — The typed api client for the backend, based at NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL (trailing slash stripped) or http://localhost:8000.
A generic request helper sends JSON, and on a non-ok response throws an Error carrying the body's detail field or the status line; a requestFiles variant defaults the optional pythonProvenance and units fields to empty arrays and the optional seeded flag to false.
Wraps every endpoint: GET /api/files by program name, POST /api/adopt with the program name, POST /api/save with partial human/context/python, a saveUnit helper POSTing /api/save-unit with the program name, unit target, and edited code through requestFiles, /api/checkout and /api/delete by kind and hash, /api/bundle by human hash, the pipeline calls /api/human-to-context, /api/human-to-split, /api/context-to-python, /api/compile, /api/compile-all (each taking human or context text plus a force flag and an optional compile language sent as a language field in the request body), and /api/reword; the filesystem calls /api/fs/tree with optional path and depth, /api/fs/read, /api/fs/write, /api/fs/create (file or dir under a parent), /api/fs/delete, and /api/fs/pick-folder; and the project calls to list, create, select, delete, rename, and wipe under /api/projects.
Exports the shared types — TreePython/TreeContext/TreeHuman for the history tree, ContextRole ("leaf" | "split" | "direct"), ContextProvenance entries with line/status/source/text and optional target and contextLine (the 1-based context line motivating a code line, null where inapplicable), CompiledUnit, the Files workspace payload with active hashes, status flags, role, provenance lists, tree, and a seeded flag, plus Bundle, FileNode, FsFile, FsEntry, PickedFolder, Project, and ProjectList — and the DEFAULT_PROGRAM name "program".
Also exports the COMPILE_LANGUAGES const tuple (python, typescript, tsx, javascript, css, json, html, markdown), the CompileLanguage union derived from it, and DEFAULT_COMPILE_LANGUAGE set to python, which the compile-family wrappers use as their default language argument.
